wiki.text:
'Levelling' (or 'leveling' in American spelling) is a branch of surveying, the
object of which is to #Find the elevation of a given point with respect to the
given or assumed Datum. #Establish a point at a given elevation with respect to
the given or assumed Datum.

'Levelling' is the measurement of geodetic height using an optical levelling
instrument and a level staff or rod having a numbered scale. Common levelling
instruments include the spirit level, the dumpy level, the digital level, and
the laser level.
wiki.title: Levelling
